<TEXT>
a fiveheaded khmer bust of siva the hindu god of 
destruction and reproduction has sold for 574200 an auction 
record for any southeast asian work of art at auction sothebys 
said 
the 31inch high gray sandstone bust was sold monday by an 
anonynmous collector and bought by an unidentified overseas bidder 
the figure dated from the third quarter of the 10th century no 
history of it was otherwise recorded except that the uppermost head 
had been in the pan asian collection most of which is in the los 
angeles county museum 
each of the heads wears an enigmatic smile the uppermost head 
was acquired by the seller who reunited it with the rest of the 
figure 
the sale at mondays auction of some 100 lots of khmer thai 
indian and himalayan art totaled 28 million the three toppriced 
lots were sold by the same collector 
a 7th century head of buddha from thailand larger than lifesize 
was bought for 376200 by a swiss collector another anonymous 
buyer paid a similar price for a 4foot standing figure of a khmer 
fourarmed male deity from the first half of the 9th century 
the bidders included american and swiss collectors and london 
dealers 
