<TEXT>
soviet officials who once criticized the american 
space shuttle as wasteful and unreliable joined the shuttle 
business today with a craft that looks conspiciously like its us 
predecessor 
the official tass news agency even acknowledged similarities 
between the crafts after its space plane the buran made its maiden 
unmanned flight today 
in appearance the buran resembles the us space shuttle which 
has the same streamlined forms and doubledelta wing the laws of 
aerodynamics are international it said 
despite the similarity in appearance and design however the 
soviets seem to have settled on different uses for their shuttle 
named the buran which is russian for snowstorm 
for years the soviets wouldnt even admit they were developing 
their own shuttle though western specialists date the program back 
to at least 1982 
in june 1980 10 months before the united states launched its 
first shuttle the columbia the chief of soviet cosmonaut training 
vladimir a shatalov said soviet officials consider that the 
employment of these spacecraft is not justified for soviet research 
because present tasks can be solved with the welltested methods in 
an economical way 
former cosmonaut konstantin p feoktistov writing in 1984 in a 
soviet newspaper praised the american shuttle as an impressive 
engineering achievement but he added this system is not sound 
economically and technologically 
soviet officials appeared to become believers after settling on a 
different focus for their shuttle than the one nasa chose 
the us shuttle was designed primarily to ferry satellites into 
orbit but alexander i dunayev the head of the soviet space agency 
glavkosmos said in 1987 that shuttles are not as economical as 
singleuse rocket boosters for placing satellites into orbit 
in the clearest hint of the soviet shuttles purpose he said 
such craft are valuable for servicing space stations and satellites 
and recovering objects from orbit 
the reasoning seems sound because ever since they pioneered space 
flight with the 1957 launch of sputnik the soviets have forged a 
proven track record for launching satellites on singleuse rockets 
they put up more than 150 satellites a year more than any other 
country 
in addition the soviets have concentrated on maintaining a 
permanent manned presence in space aboard the orbiting space station 
mir while soviet officials have not said whether the shuttle is 
capable of doing so the shuttle might be able to ferry supplies and 
cosmonauts to mir 
the buran might also have the capability to retrieve and repair 
potentially dangerous satellites in orbit 
the soviets have repeatedly criticized the military use of the 
american shuttle and the next american flight of the atlantis in 
late november is a mission for the pentagon 
but as with the american shuttle the soviets might use the buran 
for military missions the us defense department says the soviet 
shuttle could be used to deploy antisatellite and ballistic missile 
defense weapons 
it isnt clear whether the soviets will try to market their 
shuttles services to foreign customers as they have done with 
their proton rocket boosters if foreign customers are sought 
competition will come not only from the united states but from 
western europe 
the european space agency hopes to have its version of the 
shuttle the hermes on the launch pad in the late 1990s 
the buran clearly has advantages over its american cousin its 
separate booster rocket the energia is powered only by liquid 
fuels which can be extinguished in an emergency it has no 
solidfuel boosters like the one that failed on the challenger 
killing seven crewmembers 
in addition the soviet shuttle can use jet engines in its tail 
giving it more maneuverability in landing than its american 
counterpart 
the buran can also carry far heavier payloads than the american 
shuttle energia can hoist more than 100 tons and the orbiter 
itself can carry about 66000 pounds the us shuttle can carry 
about 55000 pounds 
while soviet officials maintain they did not copy the american 
shuttle the pentagon has a different view 
by using us propulsion computer materials and airframe 
technology and design the soviets were able to produce an orbiter 
years earlier and at far less cost than if they had depended 
solely on their own technology and engineering the defense 
department said in its 1988 report soviet military power 
</TEXT>
