<TEXT>
a planetarium whose original projector made 
viewers dizzy and ill is opening nine years late with a 68footwide 
dome and a projection system intended to simulate space travel 
the arnim d hummel planetarium officially opens wednesday at 
eastern kentucky university 
i always thought it would actually happen but i didnt think 
it would take as long as it did said jack fletcher who was hired 
11 years ago as planetarium director 
equipment installed in 1979 projected images so blurred that 
people who watched test programs became dizzy and nauseated 
the university sued the manufacturer of the projection equipment 
spitz inc of chadds ford pa two years ago spitz agreed out of 
court to replace the original equipment with a new system called 
space voyager 
in most planetariums the same projector produces images of the 
stars and planets that makes the planetariums earthbound only 
able to project the sky as it appears from the earth 
with the space voyager system the projectors are separated 
making possible the illusion of space travel 
the starball projector is 4 feet in diameter and projects 10164 
stars each star has a separate lens there are five planet 
projectors and a sun projector also part of the system are a 
multiimage slide projector and a sixchannel stereo sound system 
the system is the third of its kind in the world the others are 
in paris and singapore 
the planetarium is named for the first chairman of easterns 
physics department during world war ii hummel was instrumental in 
developing a radaractivated fuse 
the universitys planetarium is the 10thlargest of the 985 
planetariums in the united states the largest is the reuben h 
fleet space theater in san diego which has a 75foot dome 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

