<TEXT>
in asking nicholas brady to stay on as treasury 
secretary george bush has turned again to a longtime personal 
friend to staff a key cabinet post 
last week bush announced as his first cabinet appointment his 
choice of james a baker iii to be secretary of state 
while baker is the better known because of his service with bush 
in the reagan administration brady is just as close to the 
presidentelect 
earlier this year brady baker and another close bush friend 
houston oil millionaire robert a mosbacher sr were dubbed the big 
three in the bush presidential campaign the longtime friends whose 
counsel bush listened to most often 
there is speculation that mosbacher may become commerce secretary 
with bushs support brady 58 got the nod from president reagan 
to become treasury secretary when baker announced in august that he 
was leaving the administration to formally become chairman of the 
bush presidential campaign brady was sworn in as the nations 68th 
treasury secretary on sept 15 
in his first two months brady has adopted a lowkey approach 
which emphasized keeping the economy on track and avoiding any 
controversy that might stir up financial markets before the nov 8 
election 
with the election over brady is expected to move just as 
cautiously many are looking for baker to continue to play a major 
role in setting the economic as well as the foreign policy course 
for the new administration 
many of bakers major economic initiatives at treasury were in 
the foreign policy area it was baker who three years ago launched 
an initiative with major us allies to coordinate economic policies 
in an effort to lower americas huge foreigntrade deficit 
that coordination had at its heart a sharp devaluation in the 
value of the dollar to stem a flood of foreign products into the 
country by making them more expensive while reducing the cost of 
american products on overseas markets 
while the dollar devaluation has shown results america and its 
allies are now concerned that financial markets might push the 
dollar down too far in value raising the specter of higher interest 
rates and a possible recession in this country 
even the mention last week by sometime bush economic adviser 
martin feldstein that the dollar needed to drop further to cure 
americas trade problems was enough to send the greenback and the 
stock market plunging 
brady issued a statement monday that the administration was not 
abandoning its committment to stabilize the value of the dollar and 
his comments along with those of bush during a beachside interview 
calmed the markets experts are looking for no change from the baker 
policy in this area 
on another international matter brady has voiced support for 
bakers plan to revitalize lending to third world countries 
however the effort has fallen far short of expectations and many 
believe that japan france and other countries will force the bush 
administration to acknowledge next year that more needs to be done 
in the area of debt forgiveness 
events are also likely to force brady to quickly address the 
savings and loan crisis where estimates of the cost of bailing out 
hundreds of insolvent institutions have skyrocketed to between 50 
billion and 100 billion brady has already appointed a treasury 
task force to study the problem 
another treasury study group is looking at the capital gains tax 
and this too is likely to be a priority in the new administration 
bush campaigned on a pledge to cut the capital gains tax which 
is levied on profits from the sale of stocks real estate and other 
investments the top rate is 33 percent the same as for salary 
income and bush proposed cutting it to 15 percent prompting the 
charge from democratic presidential candidate michael dukakis that 
such a cut represented a giveaway to the rich 
brady has discussed capital gains taxreduction proposals with 
top aides and reportedly favors the idea of a slidingscale tax 
that would allow the rate to decline the longer the asset had been 
held 
brady is a millionaire whose upbringing and ivy league education 
closely resemble those of bush 
he entered yale one year after bush graduated he went on to get 
a masters degree in business at harvard and then became an 
investment banker in new york spending an entire career since 1954 
at dillon read amp co where he was known as a rainmaker someone 
who could attract big clients to the firm 
brady was appointed to serve out the senate term of new jersey 
democrat harrison a williams jr who resigned in march 1982 
following his conviction in the abscam scandal 
he did not seek election to the post but he remained active 
politically as a troubleshooter for the reagan administration 
serving in 1983 on three different advisory commissions on the mx 
missile central america and foreign aid 
when the stock market suffered its record plunge last year 
reagan again turned to brady giving him the job of heading a white 
house panel that investigated the market meltdown 
he and the other task force members had only 60 days to figure 
out what went wrong and recommend ways to fix it one of the first 
reports written on the crash the brady report is still widely 
regarded as the best 
the administration however almost immediately distanced itself 
from bradys main recommendation a call for the federal reserve to 
coordinate regulation of financial markets 
but during his confirmation hearing in september brady hewed to 
the administrations freemarket line saying he was satisfied with 
the administrations approach even though his own proposals were 
much tougher 
brady was born in new york city in 1930 and grew up on a large 
estate in far hills nj his familys wealth gave him a substantial 
start in business 
his grandfather who had arrived from ireland during the mid19th 
century potato famine started several electric utilities that later 
became part of the consolidated edison co of new york 
bradys close friendship with bush dates back to the early 1970s 
when the two men became better acquainted through bushs brother 
jonathan when bush left the cia in 1976 brady tried to recuit him 
as a partner at dillon read but bush turned down his friends offer 
