slightly radioactive water spilled at 
the oyster creek nuclear plant tuesday forcing officials to declare 
the lowest of four emergency categories 
nobody was contaminated and no injuries were reported said plant 
spokesman sandy polon 
the water spilled onto a reactor floor when a seal that is 
normally used to cap the flow failed during maintenance polon said 
about six employees were working on the device when the water 
spilled 
the accident prompted declaration of an unusual event 
because water flow exceeded the normal 25 gallons per minute polon 
said estimating the flow at between 25 and 50 gallons per minute 
the declaration the lowest of four emergency categories began 
at 240 am and ended at 430 am polon said 
about 10000 gallons of water were collected before repairs were 
completed polon said the water went into the plants drainage 
system where it was recirculated 
