with varying success new video remembrances of 
john f kennedy reflect the magic and the fears of his 1000 days in 
the white house 
theyre most effective when they show the young president 
speaking for himself in the witty repartee at news conferences 
for instance and when they let realtime recordings register the 
grief at his death a reporters voice breaking as he dictates from 
dallas a waiter sobbing into a starched napkin at the luncheon 
where jfk was headed that day 
